reviews.review: I felt like this movie to a step back and lacked character development for many characters made over the past 3 movies.

As hyped as this movie was I found it to be dull and kinda boring.
Don't get me wrong its a OK movie but I personally don't think this movie was necessary to be made. The previous film had a great ending that fit the characters but I guess this one is more poetic. 

I wouldn't tell someone its terrible and not to watch it but I also would not recommend it to someone unless they asked about it. 

6/10

I have to say for me this film was the worst in the Toy Story franchise. I do agree it is heartwarming and it is beautifully animated but for everything else, I feel it's lacking. I didn't feel entertained throughout the movie. The only thing keeping me in my seat would've had to of been the name Toy Story in the title.

It was very cool to have a bit of Bo Peep's story unveiled after she was "sold" in Toy Story 3. I feel all the other characters were lacking their normal traits. Even Buzz didn't act like his normal self or even his space ranger self. Barely any of the old characters featured in this film which is what I feel was lacking a lot. It was Bo, Andy and the new characters, that's it.

2 and a half stars from me. It's something that I can sit there and watch but won't enjoy watching it.
